                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4248: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-08T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 9—7:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. Peking Government has for the time being virtually ceased to function;
                    Premier is still in Tientsin, his position unchanged. The <pb facs="0809"
                        n="689" xml:id="pg_689"/> Minister of Communications is in Tientsin or
                    Mukden plotting in Fengtien-Chihli dispute. Minister of Education refused to
                    assume that office on account of financial difficulties of his Ministry.
                    Minister of War is at Mukden intriguing for the support of Chang Tso-lin to
                    secure Premiership; Minister and Vice Minister of Finance have tendered
                    resignations and gone to Tientsin, and Ministry of Finance is practically
                    non-operative. See my 86, March 8, 1 p.m.<note n="21" xml:id="d425fn21">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
